HEADWORD: Wood-note
<hw>Wood"-note`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Wood</ets>,
n. + <ets>note</ets>.]</ety> <def>A wild or natural note, as of a forest
bird.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Or sweetest Shakespeare, fancy's child,⟦br⟧
Warble his native <qex>wood-notes</qex> wild.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Wood partridge</ent>⟦br⟧
